{
  "designRationale": {
    "layoutDecisions": "The layout is structured vertically to accommodate the list of notifications efficiently on mobile screens. The top bar and bottom navigation are placed at the top and bottom, respectively, providing a clear and familiar navigation pattern.  Item spacing is set to 0 to maximize screen real estate utilization.",
    "userFlowReasoning": "The user flow is designed for quick scanning and tapping. Each notification item is presented in a concise manner, allowing for quick assessment. Tapping on a notification item leads to the respective details view. The user can easily navigate to other sections of the app via the bottom navigation.",
    "componentChoices": "I chose '10:10214' (list-item) for displaying notifications because it provides a flexible structure for the required content elements (user avatar, title, description, timestamp). It's superior to '147:3743' (product card) which is visually unsuitable for notifications and lacks the necessary text layers for this context, and '10:3856' (snackbar) which is designed for short, transient messages rather than a persistent list of notifications.",
    "visualHierarchy": "The visual hierarchy is established by using clear visual distinctions between notification items. The emphasis is on readability and scannability, with a concise presentation of essential notification details. The use of list item components naturally allows for good hierarchy based on position.",
    "variantSelectionRationale": "For the list-item component, I selected 'Condition=2-line', 'Leading=Image', 'Trailing=None', 'Show overline=False', 'Show supporting text=True' variants.  'Condition=2-line' is chosen as notifications might require two lines for adequate description. 'Leading=Image' displays the user avatar. 'Trailing=None' avoids unnecessary visual clutter.  'Show overline=False' simplifies the look. 'Show supporting text=True' allows for inclusion of the timestamp. Other options were rejected because they are not visually appropriate or not relevant given the available content."
  }
}
